# SOC Role in Blue Team

## What I learned
- Security teams can vary in structure depending on the size and maturity of an organization.
- The SOC is part of the Blue Team and consists of multiple roles working together to defend against threats.
- The CIRT (Computer Incident Response Team) handles major incidents when the SOC cannot fully contain or resolve them.
- Larger organizations may have additional supporting teams and specialized roles.
- SOC environments can be either internal or provided by an MSSP (Managed Security Service Provider).

## Key concepts
- Red Team is responsible for offensive security (simulated attacks).
- GRC (Governance, Risk, and Compliance) manages policies, risk, and regulatory compliance.
- Blue Team is responsible for defensive security and protecting systems.
- SOC typically includes L1/L2/L3 analysts, engineers, and managers.
- MSSP provides outsourced security monitoring and services.


## Why it matters in SOC
- A SOC needs clear structure and defined roles to effectively detect, respond to, and manage security incidents.

## Commands / tools used
-  Completed a scenario-based exercise identifying which team members respond to different types of security incidents.

## Personal notes
- I learned more about how SOC teams are structured and how they interact with other security teams in an organization.
